  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN198.1-kilavi"><app><lem>puṇarntu</lem><rdg wit="#C3">iravukkuṟi puṇarntu</rdg></app> nīṅkiya talaimakaḷatu pōkku <app><lem>nōkkit</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #RK">nōkkiya</rdg></app> talaimakaṉ <app><lem>taṉṉeñciṟkuc</lem><rdg wit="#C5">/</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to his heart when looking at HER going [away] who was leaving after the union.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN198.1">
        <l>kūṟuvaṅ kollō kūṟalaṅ kolleṉak</l>
        <l>karanta kāmaṅ kainniṟuk kallātu</l>
        <l>nayantunām viṭṭa naṉmoḻi nampi</l>
        <l>yaraināḷ yāmattu viḻumaḻai karantu</l>
        <l>kārvirai kamaḻuṅ kūnta ṟūviṉai</l>
        <l>nuṇṇū lākam poruntiṉaḷ veṟpi</l>
        <l>ṉiṉamaḻai cūḻnta maṭamayil pōla</l>
        <l>vaṇṭuvaḻip paṭarat taṇmalar vēyntu</l>
        <l>vilvakup puṟṟa nalvāṅku <supplied>ku</supplied>ṭaccū</l>
        <l>lañcilam poṭukki yañciṉaḷ vantu</l>
        <l>tuñcūr yāmattu muyaṅkiṉaḷ peyarvō</l>
        <l>ḷāṉṟa kaṟpiṟ cāṉṟa pēriya</l>
        <l>lammā varivaiyō valla ṭeṉāa</l>
        <l>tāay taṉaṉāṭ ṭaṇaṅkuṭaic cilampiṟ</l>
        <l>kaviram pēriya vurukeḻu kavā<supplied>a</supplied></l>
        <l><supplied>ṉē</supplied>rmalar niṟaiccuṉai yuṟaiyuñ</l>
        <l>cūrmakaṇ mātō veṉṉumeṉ ṉeñcē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Besides weighing in hand the hidden passion: (2)</l>
        <l>“shall we talk? Shall we not talk?”, (1)</l>
        <l>longingly trusting in the good word uttered by us, (3)</l>
        <l>hiding in the excellent rains of deep midnight (4)</l>
        <l>she with a bosom suited [to wearing] fine threads (6a-c)</l>
        <l>of pure workmanship, [her] tresses fragrant with the scent of the rainy season, (5)</l>
        <l>being covered with cool flowers, so that bees make [their] way [to them], (8)</l>
        <l>like a youthful peacock surrounded by clouds in a group on the mountain, (6df.)</l>
        <l>she who out of fear had muffled [the sound of her] pretty anklets (10a-c)</l>
        <l>of well-curved Kuṭaccūl [type] that have bow[like-] divisions, (9)</l>
        <l>came [and] embraced [me] at midnight as the village was sleeping [and then] went back. (10df.)</l>
        <l>“She is, is she not, not that dark woman (13a-c)</l>
        <l>of great nature abounding in noble fidelity? (12)</l>
        <l>Or is she a woman sprite (17ab)</l>
        <l>who dwells in a pool full of beautiful blossoms (16)</l>
        <l>on the fearful slope named Kaviram (15)</l>
        <l>of the haunted mountain side in the land of Āay in the South?” (13f.)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">says my heart. (17cd)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
